        Set the effective window of the version list by changing effective date, expiration date, or both. If effectiveDate is non-null, it is the new effective date of the window. If it is null, the expiration date continues to be the expiration date of the latest version currently in the list. If any versions now fall completely outside the new effective window, this method removes those versions. If any versions now cross the boundary of the new effective window, this method truncates the effective date range of those versions. If effectiveDate is before the earliest effective date in the list, this method changes the effective date of the earliest version to match the new window effective date.
